【Solution】According to the problem:
If there are 5 clubs among the 14 cards, they are all different, and the sum of the smallest 5 numbers is $1+2+3+4+5=15$;
The sum of the smallest 4 diamonds is $1+2+3+4=10$;
The sum of the smallest 3 spades is $1+2+3=6$;
The sum of the smallest 2 hearts is $1+2=3$;
$$
15+10+6+3=34 \text {. }
$$

Therefore, the answer is: 4

【Answer】 14612

【Solution】Assume $\overline{c b 0 a}=(\overline{e f})^{2}=(10 e+f)^{2}=100 e^{2}+20 e f+f^{2}(a \neq 0 \Rightarrow f \neq 0)$, taking the modulo 100 on both sides, we get $20 e f+f^{2} \equiv a(\bmod 100)$, which means the tens digit of $20 e f+f^{2}$ is 0. Clearly, the tens digit of $20 e f$ is definitely even, so the tens digit of $f^{2}$ must also be even, and the values of $f$ that satisfy this condition are $1, 2, 3, 5, 7, 8, 9$.
(1) When $f=1, 2, 3$, to make the tens digit of $20 e f+f^{2}$ 0, then $e=5$. In this case, the three numbers are $51^{2}=2501, 52^{2}=2704, 53^{2}=2809$;
(2) When $f=5$, $20 e f+f^{2}=100 e+25$, the tens digit cannot be 0;
(3) When $f=7$, $20 e f+f^{2}=140 e+49$, to make the tens digit 0, then $e=4$ or 9, in this case, the numbers that satisfy the condition are $47^{2}=2209$ or $97^{2}=9409$;
(4) When $f=8$, $20 e f+f^{2}=160 e+64$, to make the tens digit 0, then $e=4$ or 9, in this case, the numbers that satisfy the condition are $48^{2}=2304$ or $98^{2}=9604$;
(5) When $f=9$, $20 e f+f^{2}=180 e+81$, to make the tens digit 0, then $e=4$ or 9, in this case, the numbers that satisfy the condition are $49^{2}=2401$ or $99^{2}=9801$.

Thus, we have 9 numbers that satisfy the condition, which can be grouped by the last digit into three groups: $(2209,2809,9409), (2704,2304,9604), (2501,2401,9801)$. According to the second statement by $B$ and $C$, we know that the last digits of the numbers on the hats of $A, B, C$ are the same. According to the third statement by $A$, we know that these three numbers are $(2704,2304,9604)$, so the sum of these three numbers is $2704+2304+9604=14612$.
